	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64893709"><blockquote><div><p>and that hypothesis definitely is falsifiable</p></div></blockquote><p>Wrong. A statement "The X <em>could</em> happen" is not falsifiable. Whether X actually happens or not, the statement was not false.</p><p>To make it falsifiable, the "could" must be replaced with "will". Amazing, that such basics need to be explained on Slashdot...</p><p>And, yeah, most of "Climate Science" is not falsifiable &mdash; as <a href="https://theconversation.com/climate-change-has-changed-the-way-i-think-about-science-heres-why-82314" title="theconversation.com" rel="nofollow">admitted by its practitioners</a> [theconversation.com]. Which makes it not a science at all...</p></div>
	</div>

